vim cheatsheet :

vim <file_name> : for example .git/config

vim has 3 modes 

: - Command mode 
shift+i - Insert mode
esc - Last line mode


commands :

:q - quit if no changes were made
:q! - quit and destroy any changes made
:wq - write changes (save) and quit
:x - similar to :wq, only write the file if changes were made, then 
